2
1 (4) The residential rental property is being sold due to the
2 death of the owner of the residential rental property.
3 (5) The residential rental property contains more than four
4 (4) dwelling units and is used for multifamily residential
5 housing.
6 (c) Except as provided in subsection (d), a buyer of a residential
7 rental property shall honor an unexpired written lease between the
8 previous owner and a tenant.
9 (d) A buyer of a residential rental property may terminate an
10 unexpired written lease between the previous owner and a tenant
11 if the buyer:
12 (1) not less than thirty (30) days before the lease is terminated,
13 gives written notice to the tenant that the buyer intends to
14 terminate the lease; and
15 (2) pays the tenant an amount equal to:
16 (A) the amount of one (1) monthly rental payment, as
17 specified in the written lease; plus
18 (B) the amount of the full security deposit, as specified in
19 the written lease.
20 SECTION 2. IC 32-31-8-5 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
21 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) As used in this
22 section, "essential services" means:
23 (1) electricity;
24 (2) gas;
25 (3) heat;
26 (4) water; or
27 (5) other services;
28 needed for the safe and habitable occupation by a tenant of the
29 tenant's rental unit.
30 (b) As used in this section, "essential system" means a system,
31 or one (1) or more parts or components of a system, that:
32 (1) is described in subsection (c)(4); and
33 (2) is:
34 (A) used for; or
35 (B) necessary to;
36 the delivery of one (1) or more essential services to a rental
37 unit.
38 (c) A landlord shall do the following:
39 (1) Deliver the rental premises to a tenant in compliance with the
40 rental agreement, and in a safe, clean, and habitable condition.
41 (2) Comply with all health and housing codes applicable to the
42 rental premises.
