3
1 (3) Make all reasonable efforts to keep common areas of a rental
2 premises in a clean and proper condition.
3 (4) Provide and maintain the following items in a rental premises
4 in good and safe working condition, if provided on the premises
5 at the time the rental agreement is entered into:
6 (A) Electrical systems.
7 (B) Plumbing systems sufficient to accommodate a reasonable
8 supply of hot and cold running water at all times.
9 (C) Sanitary systems.
10 (D) Heating, ventilating, and air conditioning systems. A
11 heating system must be sufficient to adequately supply heat at
12 all times.
13 (E) Elevators, if provided.
14 (F) Appliances supplied as an inducement to the rental
15 agreement.
16 (5) Pay all penalties or fines imposed by a political subdivision
17 for violation of an obligation under this section with regard to
18 a rental premises. A landlord may not deliver rental premises
19 to a tenant until all penalties or fines are paid and all repairs
20 required by the political subdivision are completed.
21 (d) Subject to subsections (e) and (f), a landlord shall repair or
22 replace an essential system not later than forty-eight (48) hours
23 after being notified by a tenant that the tenant's rental unit is
24 without one (1) or more essential services as a result of:
25 (1) a malfunction in the essential system; or
26 (2) the landlord's failure to otherwise maintain the essential
27 system in good and safe working condition.
28 (e) The forty-eight (48) hour period set forth in subsection (d)
29 does not apply if:
30 (1) the tenant's rental unit is without one (1) or more essential
31 services:
32 (A) because of a malfunction in an essential system; and
33 (B) the malfunction is the direct result of the tenant's
34 commission of waste to the essential system or the rental
35 unit; or
36 (2) the landlord makes a good faith attempt within the
37 forty-eight (48) hour period set forth in subsection (d) to
38 undertake the needed repairs to, or replacement of, an
39 essential system through:
40 (A) the landlord's own efforts; or
41 (B) the services of:
42 (i) a contractor; or
